HOUSE RESOLUTION 203
By Barrett
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Dickson County High
School Lady Cougars bowling team upon
winning the TSSAA Division I, Region 6 girls'
bowling championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should salute those
student athletes who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true
champions of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of individuals is the Dickson County High School
girls' bowling team, whose members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of competitors
and truly worthy of admiration by winning the TSSAA Division I, Region 6 girls' bowling
championship held at Tenn-Pin Alley in Columbia; and
WHEREAS, Kelsey Ellison led Dickson County in the opening game of the finals with a
193, while Kya McCoy added a 186; in the second game, Ella Deems paced the Lady Cougars
with a 210, while Sami Malone rolled a 198 and Leah Schindler added a 193; and
WHEREAS, Dickson County won the first Baker-format game by two pins; the Lady
Cougars did not need to win the second Baker game to claim the championship, but could not
lose by more than twenty-four pins; and
WHEREAS, after their opponents struck all three times in the tenth frame, Dickson
County anchor bowler Sami Malone bowled three strikes to win the region championship by
three pins; and
WHEREAS, the Lady Cougars' superb performance would not have been possible
without the stellar leadership of their coaches and the unfailing support of their families, their
fans, and their community; and
HR0203
